+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xeb8bAsFKPAAnCEeapfFiG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have the complete picture. Let me provide you with a comprehensive analysis of the codebase.\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/\n│   ├── events/\n│   │   ├── types.ts          (Event interface definitions & constants)\n│   │   └── bus.ts            (Event bus implementation)\n│   ├── orders/\n│   │   ├── repository.ts      (Order data storage)\n│   │   └── service.ts         (Order business logic)\n│   ├── billing/\n│   │   ├── calculator.ts      (Price calculation logic)\n│   │   └── service.ts         (Payment processing)\n│   ├── inventory/\n│   │   ├── repository.ts      (Stock data storage)\n│   │   └── service.ts         (Stock reservation & release)\n│   ├── notifications/\n│   │   └── service.ts         (Notification sending)\n│   └── index.ts               (Public exports)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── events.test.ts\n│   ├── orders.test.ts\n│   ├── inventory.test.ts\n│   ├── billing.test.ts\n│   └── notifications.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. EVENTS SYSTEM (Core Infrastructure)\n\n### `/workspace/src/events/types.ts`\nDefines all event types and constants used throughout the system.\n\n**Key Interfaces:**\n- `OrderEvent`: Base interface with `orderId` and `timestamp`\n- `OrderCreatedEvent`: Extends OrderEvent with `items[]` and `customerId`\n- `OrderCancelledEvent`: Extends OrderEvent with `reason`\n- `OrderRefundedEvent`: Extends OrderEvent with `amount`\n- `PaymentChargedEvent`: Extends OrderEvent with `amount` and `paymentMethod`\n- `StockReservedEvent`: Extends OrderEvent with `items[]`\n\n**Event Constants (ORDER_EVENTS):**\n```\nCREATED: 'order.created'\nCONFIRMED: 'order.confirmed'\nCANCELLED: 'order.cancelled'\nREFUNDED: 'order.refunded'\nPAYMENT_CHARGED: 'order.payment.charged'\nSTOCK_RESERVED: 'order.stock.reserved'\nSTOCK_RELEASED: 'order.stock.released'\nNOTIFICATION_SENT: 'order.notification.sent'\n```\n\n### `/workspace/src/events/bus.ts`\nImplements the event bus using a global handler registry pattern.\n\n**Key Class: EventBus**\n- **Private Field:** `globalHandlers: Map<string, EventHandler[]>` (module-level, shared across instances)\n- **Methods:**\n  - `on(event: string, handler: EventHandler)`: Register event handler\n  - `off(event: string, handler: EventHandler)`: Unregister event handler\n  - `emit(event: string, data: unknown)`: Emit event to all registered handlers (async)\n  - `clear()`: Clear all handlers from global registry\n\n**Critical Note:** Uses a GLOBAL handler registry that persists across EventBus instances—this is important for understanding shared state in tests.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ORDERS SYSTEM\n\n### `/workspace/src/orders/repository.ts`\nIn-memory data storage for orders.\n\n**Types:**\n- `OrderStatus = 'pending' | 'confirmed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded'`\n- `OrderItem`: `{ productId, quantity, unitPrice }`\n- `Order`: Full order with id, customerId, items[], status, total, discount, taxRate, createdAt, updatedAt, optional notes\n\n**Key Class: OrderRepository**\n- **Private Field:** `store: Map<string, Order>`\n- **Methods:**\n  - `create(order: Order): Order` - Creates & returns copy\n  - `findById(id: string): Order | undefined` - Returns copy\n  - `update(id: string, updates: Partial<Order>): Order | undefined` - Returns copy\n  - `findByCustomer(customerId: string): Order[]` - Returns copies\n  - `findByStatus(status: OrderStatus): Order[]` - Returns copies\n  - `clear()` - Clears store\n\n---\n\n### `/workspace/src/orders/service.ts`\nMain order business logic coordinating the event-driven flow.\n\n**Constructor Dependencies:**\n- `OrderRepository`\n- `EventBus`\n- `BillingService`\n\n**Constants:**\n- `REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS = 30`\n\n**Key Methods:**\n\n**`async createOrder(id, customerId, items[], discount, taxRate)`**\n1. Creates order in repository with status 'pending'\n2. Emits `ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED` event\n3. Calls `billingService.chargePayment()` (synchronously charges)\n4. Updates order status to 'confirmed' with total\n5. Emits `ORDER_EVENTS.CONFIRMED` event\n6. Returns confirmed order\n\n**`async cancelOrder(id, reason)`**\n- Validates order exists and status is 'confirmed'\n- Emits `ORDER_EVENTS.CANCELLED` event (with items and reason)\n- Updates status to 'cancelled'\n- Returns cancelled order\n\n**`async refundOrder(id)`**\n- Validates order is 'cancelled'\n- Checks refund window (max 30 days from creation)\n- Throws error if window expired\n- Calls `billingService.issueRefund()`\n- Updates status to 'refunded'\n- Returns refunded order\n\n**`getOrder(id)` & `getOrdersByCustomer(customerId)`**: Simple queries\n\n---\n\n## 3. BILLING SYSTEM\n\n### `/workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts`\nPure calculation logic for order pricing.\n\n**Type: PriceBreakdown**\n```\n{\n  subtotal: number,\n  discountAmount: number,\n  taxAmount: number,\n  total: number\n}\n```\n\n**Function: `calculateOrderTotal(items[], discountPercent, taxRate)`**\n- Calculates subtotal from all items (quantity × unitPrice)\n- Applies percentage discount to subtotal\n- Applies tax rate to discounted amount\n- Returns breakdown with all components\n- **Important:** All values rounded to 2 decimal places using `Math.round(value * 100) / 100`\n\n---\n\n### `/workspace/src/billing/service.ts`\nPayment processing and event-driven refund handling.\n\n**Type: PaymentRecord**\n```\n{\n  orderId: string,\n  amount: number,\n  method: string,\n  status: 'charged' | 'refunded',\n  processedAt: number\n}\n```\n\n**Constructor Dependencies:**\n- `EventBus`\n- `NotificationService`\n\n**Key Methods:**\n\n**`registerHandlers()`**\n- Listens to `ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RESERVED`: Emits `PAYMENT_CHARGED` event\n- Listens to `ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED`: Calls `handleRefund` to update payment status\n\n**`async chargePayment(orderId, items[], discountPercent, taxRate, paymentMethod)`**\n- Calls `calculateOrderTotal()`\n- Creates PaymentRecord with status 'charged'\n- Stores in payments map\n- Sends confirmation notification\n- Returns PaymentRecord\n\n**`async issueRefund(orderId, amount)`**\n- Finds payment record\n- Updates status to 'refunded'\n- Emits `ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED` event\n- Returns refunded payment record\n\n**Helper Methods:**\n- `handleStockReserved()`: Emits PAYMENT_CHARGED (called by event handler)\n- `handleRefund()`: Updates payment status to refunded (called by event handler)\n- `getPayment(orderId)`: Returns payment copy\n- `clear()`: Clears payments map\n\n---\n\n## 4. INVENTORY SYSTEM\n\n### `/workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts`\nStock management with reservation tracking.\n\n**Type: StockRecord**\n```\n{\n  productId: string,\n  available: number,\n  reserved: number\n}\n```\n\n**Key Class: InventoryRepository**\n\n**Methods:**\n\n**`setStock(productId, quantity)`**\n- Creates/updates stock record with available quantity\n- Preserves existing reserved count\n\n**`reserve(productId, quantity): boolean`**\n- Returns false if insufficient available stock\n- Otherwise decrements available, increments reserved\n- Returns true on success\n\n**`release(productId, quantity): boolean`**\n- Returns false if reserved < quantity\n- Otherwise increments available, decrements reserved\n- Returns true on success\n\n**`getStock(productId): StockRecord | undefined`** - Returns copy\n\n**`clear()`** - Clears store\n\n---\n\n### `/workspace/src/inventory/service.ts`\nEvent-driven stock reservation and release logic.\n\n**Constructor Dependencies:**\n- `InventoryRepository`\n- `EventBus`\n\n**Key Methods:**\n\n**`registerHandlers()`**\n- Listens to `ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED`: Calls `handleOrderCreated`\n- Listens to `ORDER_EVENTS.CANCELLED`: Calls `handleOrderCancelled`\n\n**`async handleOrderCreated(event: OrderCreatedEvent)`**\n- Iterates through event items\n- For each item, calls `repo.reserve(productId, quantity)`\n- **If any reservation fails:**\n  - Rolls back all previous reservations\n  - Throws error: \"Insufficient stock for product {productId}\"\n- If all succeed: Emits `ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RESERVED` event\n\n**`async handleOrderCancelled(event: OrderCancelledEvent & { items?, status? })`**\n- Only processes if event.status === 'cancelled'\n- For each item, calls `repo.release(productId, quantity)`\n- Emits `ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RELEASED` event\n\n**`setStock(productId, quantity)` & `getStock(productId)`** - Delegates to repository\n\n---\n\n## 5. NOTIFICATIONS SYSTEM\n\n### `/workspace/src/notifications/service.ts`\nNotification templates and sending.\n\n**Type: NotificationRecord**\n```\n{\n  type: string,\n  orderId: string,\n  message: string,\n  sentAt: number\n}\n```\n\n**Key Class: NotificationService**\n\n**Templates Map:**\n```\n'order.confirmed': 'Your order {orderId} has been confirmed. Total: ${total}'\n'order.cancelled': 'Your order {orderId} has been cancelled. Reason: {reason}'\n'order.refunded': 'Your refund of ${amount} for order {orderId} has been processed.'\n```\n\n**Key Methods:**\n\n**`sendConfirmation(orderId, total): NotificationRecord`**\n- Replaces template placeholders\n- Creates record with type='confirmation'\n- Stores in sent array\n- Returns record\n\n**`sendCancellation(orderId, reason): NotificationRecord`**\n- Similar flow, type='cancellation'\n\n**`sendRefundNotice(orderId, amount): NotificationRecord`**\n- Similar flow, type='refund'\n\n**`getSentNotifications(): NotificationRecord[]`** - Returns copy of sent array\n\n**`clear()`** - Clears sent array\n\n---\n\n## 6. EVENT FLOW ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Order Creation Flow (Happy Path)\n```\nOrderService.createOrder()\n  ↓ (1) Save pending order\n  ↓ (2) Emit ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED\n    ↓ InventoryService.handleOrderCreated()\n      ↓ Reserve stock for each item (with rollback on failure)\n      ↓ Emit ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RESERVED\n        ↓ BillingService.handleStockReserved()\n          ↓ Emit ORDER_EVENTS.PAYMENT_CHARGED\n  ↓ (3) billingService.chargePayment()\n    ↓ Calculate total via calculator\n    ↓ Store PaymentRecord with status='charged'\n    ↓ Send confirmation notification\n  ↓ (4) Update order status to 'confirmed'\n  ↓ (5) Emit ORDER_EVENTS.CONFIRMED\n  ↓ Return confirmed order\n```\n\n### Order Cancellation Flow\n```\nOrderService.cancelOrder()\n  ↓ Validate order is 'confirmed'\n  ↓ Emit ORDER_EVENTS.CANCELLED (with items)\n    ↓ InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled()\n      ↓ Release stock for each item\n      ↓ Emit ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RELEASED\n  ↓ Update order status to 'cancelled'\n  ↓ Return cancelled order\n```\n\n### Order Refund Flow\n```\nOrderService.refundOrder()\n  ↓ Validate order is 'cancelled' and within 30-day window\n  ↓ billingService.issueRefund()\n    ↓ Update PaymentRecord status to 'refunded'\n    ↓ Emit ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED\n      ↓ BillingService.handleRefund()\n        ↓ Send refund notification\n  ↓ Update order status to 'refunded'\n  ↓ Return refunded order\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. COMPLETE TEST SUITE BREAKDOWN\n\n### `/workspace/tests/events.test.ts`\n**EventBus Tests (5 tests)**\n1. Emits events to registered handlers\n2. Supports multiple handlers for same event\n3. Does not fire handlers for different events\n4. Removes handlers with off()\n5. Clears all handlers\n\n### `/workspace/tests/orders.test.ts`\n**OrderService Tests (6 tests)**\n1. Creates order and confirms it (total=55 from items totaling 50 + 10% tax)\n2. Reserves stock when order is created\n3. Cancels confirmed order\n4. Releases stock when order is cancelled\n5. Refuses to cancel non-confirmed order\n6. Refunds cancelled order within 30 days\n7. Allows refund on exactly day 30\n8. Rejects refund after 30-day window (31+ days)\n\n**OrderRepository Tests (4 tests)**\n1. Creates and retrieves order\n2. Update preserves other fields\n3. Returns undefined for missing order\n4. Finds orders by customer\n\n### `/workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts`\n**InventoryService Tests (5 tests)**\n1. Reserves stock on order.created event\n2. Throws when stock insufficient\n3. Rolls back partial reservations on failure\n4. Releases stock on order.cancelled event\n5. Reserves stock for concurrent orders independently\n\n### `/workspace/tests/billing.test.ts`\n**calculateOrderTotal Tests (4 tests)**\n1. Calculates total with no discount/tax\n2. Applies percentage discount before tax (e.g., $100 - 10% + 8% tax = $97.20)\n3. Handles multiple items with discount and tax\n4. Rounds correctly for penny-edge amounts\n\n**BillingService Tests (4 tests)**\n1. Charges payment and records it\n2. Sends confirmation notification on charge\n3. Issues refund and updates payment status\n4. Sends refund notification\n\n### `/workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts`\n**NotificationService Tests (4 tests)**\n1. Sends order confirmation\n2. Sends cancellation notice\n3. Sends refund notice\n4. Tracks all sent notifications\n\n---\n\n## 8. KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n### Event-Driven Architecture\n- **Decoupling:** Services communicate via events instead of direct calls\n- **Global EventBus:** Shared across all services via dependency injection\n- **Async Handlers:** Event handlers can be async, awaited in sequence\n\n### Repository Pattern\n- **Data Abstraction:** OrderRepository, InventoryRepository isolate data storage\n- **Immutability:** All methods return copies to prevent external mutations\n- **In-Memory Storage:** Using Map for test-friendly persistence\n\n### Pure Functions\n- **Billing Calculator:** `calculateOrderTotal()` is pure, no side effects\n- **Deterministic:** Same inputs always produce same outputs\n\n### Transactional Logic\n- **Stock Reservation:** Rollback on failure prevents partial reservations\n- **Refund Window:** Business rule enforced (30-day limit)\n\n---\n\n## 9. IMPORTANT DETAILS FOR DEBUGGING\n\n### Potential Bug Areas (Based on Architecture)\n1. **EventBus Global State:** Handlers persist across instances—test isolation issues possible if clear() not called\n2. **Async Event Handling:** Events are awaited sequentially—order matters\n3. **Refund Window Calculation:** Uses `Math.floor((Date.now() - createdAt) / (1000*60*60*24))`—off-by-one possible at boundaries\n4. **Stock Reservation Rollback:** Must succeed fully or fail completely—partial state invalid\n5. **Payment Status Management:** Separate from order status—can diverge\n6. **Notification Templates:** String replacement with `{placeholder}` and `${placeholder}` syntax\n\n### Data Flow Guarantees\n- **Orders:** Flow through states: pending → confirmed → cancelled/refunded\n- **Stock:** Moves from available → reserved → available (on release)\n- **Payments:** Flow through: charged → refunded\n- **Notifications:** One-way fire-and-forget (no error handling in handlers)\n\n---\n\n## 10. PUBLIC API (from /workspace/src/index.ts)\n\n**Exported Classes:**\n- `EventBus`\n- `OrderRepository`, `OrderService`\n- `InventoryRepository`, `InventoryService`\n- `BillingService`, `calculateOrderTotal`\n- `NotificationService`\n\n**Exported Types:**\n- `OrderEvent`, `OrderCreatedEvent`, `OrderCancelledEvent`, `OrderRefundedEvent`, `PaymentChargedEvent`, `StockReservedEvent`\n- `Order`, `OrderItem`, `OrderStatus`\n- `StockRecord`\n- `PaymentRecord`\n- `NotificationRecord`\n- `PriceBreakdown`\n\n---\n\nThis is a comprehensive event-driven order processing system with clear separation of concerns, using the pub/sub pattern via EventBus for service communication. All business logic is well-tested with 23 total test cases covering the happy paths and edge cases."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2465d0 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 32752\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 45823</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"040d03dc-2e68-44d2-9401-fdb225cae40e","uuid":"7b1ed8a1-c19d-43c1-a9b4-24d0c9e5d432","tool_use_result":{"status":"compl